Multimodal model Scope:¶

The scope of this notebook is to create the classification model to classify the tumors in three classes (response, non-response and stable). We will use elastography images as input to the first channel of the multimodal and for the second channel tabular data with information on perfused area and cell line type. The goal is to find how strong is the relation between the three classes and the tumor characteristics. In other words to identify which features/attributes (elastic modulus, perfused area, cell line, therapy, stresses) contributed the most to the prediction of the class.

Found 1365 images belonging to 3 classes.

Shear Wave Elastography (SWE) images¶

Here we show the image data that we will use in our multimoodal, alongside their label (Response, Stable, non-Response)¶

Found 1365 images belonging to 3 classes.

We have 1365 total observations

XG Boost model interpretability¶

As expected elastic modulus and normalized perfused area are the most important features for the predictions. K7M2 and MCA205 has no significant value on predicting the class which makes sense considering their limited number of observations, especially in the test set.
